Former president Jacob Zuma faces 16 charges charges of corruption, money laundering, fraud and racketeering. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 PIETERMARITZBURG - Former president, Jacob Zuma's corruption trial has been postponed to 26 May 2021. This for him to enter his formal plea. READ: De Lille expected first witness as Zuma corruption trial resumes He faces 16 charges charges of corruption, money laundering, fraud and racketeering. Zuma is being represented by Advocate Thabani Masuku.